text.tspan: The World's Population: the last 65 years and the next 65 years
The world's population will grow from 7.3 billion to over 10 million by 2056. Most of the growth will come from Africa's booming population.
Regional Contribution to the World's Population
The global population will comprise greater percentages of Africans and lower percentages of Europeans and Asians in the next 65 years.
